1
00:00:04,005 --> 00:00:06,440
(Mitsui) Let's start. ⟨The stage is one of Japan's most famous celebrity hospitals⟩

2
00:00:06,507 --> 00:00:08,943
⟨There, a team is secretly formed⟩

3
00:00:09,009 --> 00:00:10,945
(Kamiya) Mother and child life-saving emergency class.

4
00:00:11,012 --> 00:00:14,949
⟨Their mission is to save pregnant women who have nowhere to go for free⟩

5
00:00:15,015 --> 00:00:16,450
(Mitsui) Cardiac arrest!

6
00:00:16,517 --> 00:00:18,452
Don't leave the baby alone.

7
00:00:18,519 --> 00:00:20,454
Come back!

8
00:00:20,521 --> 00:00:21,956
please.

9
00:00:22,023 --> 00:00:24,024
(May) Excuse me.

10
00:00:33,534 --> 00:00:36,036
(Nagasaka) [Sorry, I'm in a hurry]

11
00:00:44,045 --> 00:00:46,480
(Nao) It's been a while... right.

12
00:00:46,547 --> 00:00:48,983
(Mitsui) Huh? acquaintance?

13
00:00:49,049 --> 00:00:51,485
(Nao) My classmate from high school.

14
00:00:51,552 --> 00:00:55,990
I left school before my second year, so it was only for a short time.

15
00:00:56,057 --> 00:00:59,994
(May) Is this the person you were talking to before?

16
00:01:00,060 --> 00:01:01,996
(Kurata) Mr. Nagasaka.

17
00:01:02,062 --> 00:01:04,498
(Kurata) Isn't there something like "How have you been?"

18
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:08,436
(Nagasaka) Gee... How have you been?

19
00:01:08,502 --> 00:01:10,438
>>Yes.

20
00:01:10,504 --> 00:01:12,940
(Mitsui) Please take care of me.

21
00:01:13,007 --> 00:01:14,508
(May) Yes.

22
00:01:17,011 --> 00:01:20,448
(May) This hospital is very splendid.

23
00:01:20,514 --> 00:01:23,951
I'll give you my money back someday.

24
00:01:24,018 --> 00:01:27,455
But right now, there really isn't much.

25
00:01:27,521 --> 00:01:31,459
(Mitsui) It's okay, it's my house.

26
00:01:31,525 --> 00:01:34,462
(Narumiya) Please sign here.

27
00:01:34,528 --> 00:01:45,473
♪～

28
00:01:45,539 --> 00:01:47,541
(Mitsui) It's the 29th week.

29
00:01:49,043 --> 00:01:50,978
(May) What happened to my baby→

30
00:01:51,045 --> 00:01:54,982
I couldn't tell anyone.

31
00:01:55,049 --> 00:01:58,986
The other person is a technical intern like me.

32
00:01:59,053 --> 00:02:03,424
We didn't know what to do.

33
00:02:03,491 --> 00:02:06,927
If the company finds out, you won't be able to stay there.

34
00:02:06,994 --> 00:02:09,430
(Kurata) Legally I can't fire you, but →

35
00:02:09,497 --> 00:02:14,435
I hear that the reality is that you will eventually have no choice but to quit.

36
00:02:14,502 --> 00:02:17,938
It's all thanks to Nao.

37
00:02:18,005 --> 00:02:28,449
♪～

38
00:02:28,516 --> 00:02:31,452
[Mei]

39
00:02:31,519 --> 00:02:33,954
[I got it]

40
00:02:34,021 --> 00:02:36,457
[There's a baby, right?]

41
00:02:36,524 --> 00:02:40,461
(Mei's voice) Find a place where Nao can help →

42
00:02:40,528 --> 00:02:43,964
I was able to come to this hospital.

43
00:02:44,031 --> 00:02:48,469
And I'm talking to the company right now.

44
00:02:48,536 --> 00:02:51,472
Born in Japan →

45
00:02:51,539 --> 00:02:54,475
So that I can continue working after this.

46
00:02:54,542 --> 00:02:58,979
(Mitsui) Mei-san, are you interested in this?

47
00:02:59,046 --> 00:03:00,481
>> Huh?

48
00:03:00,548 --> 00:03:02,917
(Mitsui) Is it possible that you feel uncomfortable?

49
00:03:02,983 --> 00:03:07,421
(May) Yes, it hurts a little here.

50
00:03:07,488 --> 00:03:10,424
Sometimes it feels bad.

51
00:03:10,491 --> 00:03:12,426
(Mitsui) Please let me confirm.

52
00:03:12,493 --> 00:03:13,928
>> Yes.

53
00:03:13,994 --> 00:03:32,012
♪～

54
00:03:36,016 --> 00:03:40,521
(Nagasaka) Huh... what are you doing now?

55
00:03:42,523 --> 00:03:46,460
>> I work part-time and specialize in clothing.

56
00:03:46,527 --> 00:03:51,966
(Nagasaka) Ah, to make that dream of being a designer you talked about come true?

57
00:03:52,032 --> 00:03:55,469
>> Are you relieved that I'm getting better?

58
00:03:55,536 --> 00:03:57,972
I'm not bad.

59
00:03:58,038 --> 00:04:01,041
Yeah, it's not bad at all.

60
00:04:02,543 --> 00:04:04,478
but….

61
00:04:05,980 --> 00:04:08,415
You became a doctor.

62
00:04:08,482 --> 00:04:18,425
♪～

63
00:04:18,492 --> 00:04:21,428
(Kurata) Huh? What about Mr. Nagasaka?

64
00:04:21,495 --> 00:04:23,430
Apparently he had something urgent to do.

65
00:04:23,497 --> 00:04:26,934
There was clearly some suspicious behavior.

66
00:04:27,001 --> 00:04:30,938
(Mitsui) Mr. Mei, please listen carefully to what I am about to say.

67
00:04:31,005 --> 00:04:33,440
>> Yes.

68
00:04:33,507 --> 00:04:38,946
(Mitsui) The area that sends blood to the spleen is large like a bump.

69
00:04:39,013 --> 00:04:40,948
This is called an aneurysm.

70
00:04:41,015 --> 00:04:44,952
Increased amount of hormonal blood produced during pregnancy

71
00:04:45,019 --> 00:04:49,456
It is thought that this is caused by the increased force exerted on the stomach.

72
00:04:49,523 --> 00:04:53,460
The size of the bump now is 6cm.

73
00:04:53,527 --> 00:04:55,462
If there is a baby in the stomach as it is →

74
00:04:55,529 --> 00:04:58,966
There is a risk that the bump will grow and break.

75
00:04:59,033 --> 00:05:00,467
>> Huh?

76
00:05:00,534 --> 00:05:03,904
What happens if it breaks?

77
00:05:03,971 --> 00:05:09,410
(Mitsui) Not only the baby but also Mei will be in danger.

78
00:05:09,476 --> 00:05:11,912
(Kurata) If something were to happen, it would not be the baby →

79
00:05:11,979 --> 00:05:13,914
I decided to prioritize May's life.

80
00:05:13,981 --> 00:05:15,916
I don't like it.

81
00:05:15,983 --> 00:05:19,920
It's my dream to become a mother.

82
00:05:19,987 --> 00:05:22,923
I've always dreamed of it.

83
00:05:22,990 --> 00:05:26,927
Hold the baby with your hands.

84
00:05:26,994 --> 00:05:30,931
Let's walk together holding small hands.

85
00:05:30,998 --> 00:05:33,934
Cook me a delicious meal →

86
00:05:34,001 --> 00:05:37,004
Let's eat together and laugh.

87
00:05:39,006 --> 00:05:41,942
I don't want to lose my baby!

88
00:05:42,009 --> 00:05:44,945
please.

89
00:05:45,012 --> 00:05:47,948
please!

90
00:05:48,015 --> 00:05:53,954
(Mitsui) In that case, we will do our best to explore all possible ways.

91
00:05:54,021 --> 00:05:56,457
>> Mr. Mitsui But...

92
00:05:56,523 --> 00:06:07,901
♪～

93
00:06:07,968 --> 00:06:12,406
Can I really rely on you?

94
00:06:12,473 --> 00:06:15,909
(Mitsui) Please rely on me!

95
00:06:15,976 --> 00:06:17,911
I won't leave you alone.

96
00:06:17,978 --> 00:06:26,987
♪～

97
00:06:38,999 --> 00:06:40,934
(Higashida) The trial operation of the mother and child lifesaving project has been discontinued.

98
00:06:41,001 --> 00:06:42,936
Yes, it was decided by the board of directors.

99
00:06:43,003 --> 00:06:45,439
We are unable to examine pregnant women we accept.

100
00:06:45,506 --> 00:06:47,441
(Mitsui) I can't do it.

101
00:06:47,508 --> 00:06:49,443
>> Huh? (Mitsui) Because for pregnant women→

102
00:06:49,510 --> 00:06:51,945
I said, ``Please, please rely on me.''

103
00:06:52,012 --> 00:06:53,947
(Himejima) "Mon".

104
00:06:54,014 --> 00:06:56,950
Director Himejima. >> Yes.

105
00:06:57,017 --> 00:07:00,454
She's also a pregnant woman who hasn't been examined yet.

106
00:07:00,521 --> 00:07:04,391
What would you do if a celebrity customer found out?

107
00:07:04,458 --> 00:07:06,393
From the director still →

108
00:07:06,460 --> 00:07:09,396
I am told to help pregnant women who are in trouble.

109
00:07:09,463 --> 00:07:11,398
(Mitsui) If you want to protest, give the director a punch.

110
00:07:11,465 --> 00:07:14,401
>> You think you can't protest, right?

111
00:07:14,468 --> 00:07:16,403
Yeah, you can't.

112
00:07:16,470 --> 00:07:18,472
I've admitted it.

113
00:07:19,973 --> 00:07:22,409
Secretary General. >> He'll be gone anyway.

114
00:07:22,476 --> 00:07:23,911
Huh?

115
00:07:23,977 --> 00:07:26,914
(Nagasaka) I'm also wondering about our team.

116
00:07:26,980 --> 00:07:28,916
It is one of Japan's leading hospitals for wealthy people.

117
00:07:28,982 --> 00:07:31,418
Brand image is important and we sell safety and security →

118
00:07:31,485 --> 00:07:34,421
It is definitely not acceptable to accept pregnant women who have not been examined and are at risk of infection.

119
00:07:34,488 --> 00:07:37,424
In the first place, I came to this hospital to learn about cutting-edge infertility treatment →

120
00:07:37,491 --> 00:07:39,927
This is for the purpose of learning. Please remove me from Mei-san's charge.

121
00:07:39,993 --> 00:07:41,428
>> He speaks really fast.

122
00:07:41,495 --> 00:07:44,431
Aspects of language: from speed repetition expressions, etc.→

123
00:07:44,498 --> 00:07:47,501
You're clearly hiding your true feelings.

124
00:07:49,002 --> 00:07:52,439
Actually, there's something going on with that former classmate, right?

125
00:07:52,506 --> 00:07:53,941
(Nagasaka) What?

126
00:07:54,007 --> 00:07:56,944
>> The subtle sense of distance between the two of you is →

127
00:07:57,010 --> 00:08:02,449
Isn't this something extremely sensitive related to pregnancy?

128
00:08:02,516 --> 00:08:05,886
(Applause) Mr. Narimiya, great detective!

129
00:08:05,953 --> 00:08:07,888
No, I'm just a concierge.

130
00:08:07,955 --> 00:08:12,893
(Mitsui) Where do you feel relieved?

131
00:08:12,960 --> 00:08:14,394
(Nagasaka) Yes?

132
00:08:14,461 --> 00:08:18,899
>> The point is, where is the place where your mind is at peace?

133
00:08:18,966 --> 00:08:21,468
(Nagasaka) Ah, then...

134
00:08:28,475 --> 00:08:30,911
(Nagasaka) I wonder why you're following me now.

135
00:08:30,978 --> 00:08:33,413
(Mitsui) I have to really listen to my friends' worries.

136
00:08:33,480 --> 00:08:35,916
(Nagasaka) Mr. Hatori and Takagi. (Takagi) Because Mr. Kurata →

137
00:08:35,983 --> 00:08:38,418
Because we were recruiting. (Nagasaka) What kind of recruitment are you looking for?

138
00:08:38,485 --> 00:08:40,921
>> Life consultation at Kakinumayama!

139
00:08:40,988 --> 00:08:43,423
(All) Yay!

140
00:08:43,490 --> 00:08:45,926
(Hatori) Anyway, get to the top quickly!

141
00:08:45,993 --> 00:08:47,928
(Mitsui) Yes, let's get to the top quickly!

142
00:08:47,995 --> 00:08:49,930
(Hatori) Yay!

143
00:08:49,997 --> 00:08:51,932
a little bit….

144
00:08:51,999 --> 00:08:53,934
I can't do it anymore.

145
00:08:54,001 --> 00:08:58,939
(All) Cheers!

146
00:08:59,006 --> 00:09:01,441
\Hmm! / (Mitsui) Ah~!

147
00:09:01,508 --> 00:09:03,377
I can’t help but drink in the mountains!

148
00:09:03,443 --> 00:09:05,879
(Hatori) Craft beer in the mountains is irresistible!

149
00:09:05,946 --> 00:09:09,883
(Nagasaka) After all, the real purpose was not even to the top.

150
00:09:09,950 --> 00:09:11,885
(Mitsui) Aburi Festival!

151
00:09:11,952 --> 00:09:14,388
Grilled meat, grilled vegetables, grilled fish.

152
00:09:14,454 --> 00:09:16,390
The point is this sauce.

153
00:09:16,456 --> 00:09:19,893
Miso sauce with nuts and lemongrass fresh pepper→

154
00:09:19,960 --> 00:09:22,896
Cambodian style!

155
00:09:22,963 --> 00:09:24,898
(Khmer)

156
00:09:24,965 --> 00:09:26,400
Please!

157
00:09:26,466 --> 00:09:27,901
>> Yes, it's delicious!

158
00:09:27,968 --> 00:09:30,404
There's nothing wrong with camping food. (Mitsui) Right. >> Yeah.

159
00:09:30,470 --> 00:09:32,406
Speaking of camping, I can see Mr. Tominaga→

160
00:09:32,472 --> 00:09:34,408
Camping is my hobby.

161
00:09:34,474 --> 00:09:37,411
Also, I invited Mr. Narumiya, but he didn't come.

162
00:09:37,477 --> 00:09:39,413
His private life is quite a mystery.

163
00:09:39,479 --> 00:09:41,415
Also, Director Kamiya →

164
00:09:41,481 --> 00:09:45,919
The board may or may not issue a request for dismissal.

165
00:09:45,986 --> 00:09:47,921
(Nagasaka) The content of the conversation is too loose.

166
00:09:47,988 --> 00:09:51,425
(Mitsui) The main topic is you, please.

167
00:09:51,491 --> 00:09:52,926
(Nagasaka) "Please".

168
00:09:52,993 --> 00:09:57,431
>> Me, I heard a little story from Nao Ayukawa.

169
00:09:57,497 --> 00:09:58,932
(Nagasaka) Huh?

170
00:09:58,999 --> 00:10:03,437
>> [I got pregnant once when I was 16 years old]

171
00:10:03,503 --> 00:10:06,440
[I couldn't rely on anyone]

172
00:10:06,506 --> 00:10:08,942
[Born alone and forced into a corner→

173
00:10:09,009 --> 00:10:13,947
I left my baby outside.]

174
00:10:14,014 --> 00:10:16,950
[For Mei→

175
00:10:17,017 --> 00:10:20,454
I want the baby to be born safely.]

176
00:10:20,520 --> 00:10:25,025
He said, ``I have no intention of hiding the crime I committed.''

177
00:10:28,528 --> 00:10:30,464
(Nagasaka) That's mine.

178
00:10:30,530 --> 00:10:35,469
>> Mr. Ayukawa: Maybe he is being saved by saving Mei.

179
00:10:35,535 --> 00:10:38,038
(Nagasaka) No, that's why it's mine!

180
00:10:39,539 --> 00:10:42,976
>> So, is Mr. Ayukawa's partner Nagasaka?

181
00:10:43,043 --> 00:10:44,478
(Hatori) Let's cut into it.

182
00:10:44,544 --> 00:10:46,546
That's what I wanted to hear.

183
00:10:48,548 --> 00:10:50,484
(Nagasaka) No.

184
00:10:50,550 --> 00:10:52,486
Her parents are divorced →

185
00:10:52,552 --> 00:10:55,989
I lived with my mom who ran a snack shop.

186
00:10:56,056 --> 00:10:57,991
The other person is the customer.

187
00:10:58,058 --> 00:11:00,994
>>Then I liked her.

188
00:11:01,061 --> 00:11:03,930
But I ended up having a child with someone I don't know.

189
00:11:03,997 --> 00:11:06,500
Shock?

190
00:11:08,001 --> 00:11:10,937
(Kurata) Judging from the reaction, is that it? (Hatori) Cut in. Cut in.

191
00:11:11,004 --> 00:11:14,941
(Nagasaka) Anyway, she doesn't want me to get involved either →

192
00:11:15,008 --> 00:11:17,944
Please remove Mei from her responsibility.

193
00:11:18,011 --> 00:11:20,447
Mr. Mitsui.

194
00:11:20,514 --> 00:11:22,449
(Mitsui) Huh? What are you talking about?

195
00:11:22,516 --> 00:11:24,451
(Nagasaka) So this is a matter that Mei-san is in charge of.

196
00:11:24,518 --> 00:11:29,456
(Mitsui) Hmm, I understand. Then, please take care of that as well.

197
00:11:29,523 --> 00:11:31,458
(Nagasaka) I don't understand at all.

198
00:11:31,525 --> 00:11:34,961
I said I came here to learn about infertility treatment.

199
00:11:35,028 --> 00:11:38,465
(Mitsui) Well, please help me with that too.

200
00:11:38,532 --> 00:11:40,967
(Nagasaka) Yes?

201
00:11:41,034 --> 00:11:45,472
(Mitsui) Ms. Mei is suffering from a pregnancy complication, a giant splenic artery aneurysm.

202
00:11:45,539 --> 00:11:47,974
I'm looking for a way to save both mother and child. (Todo) Hey.

203
00:11:48,041 --> 00:11:49,976
(Todo) I heard that the trial operation of the project has been discontinued.

204
00:11:50,043 --> 00:11:52,479
What's going on? (Mitsui) I will have Mei-san hospitalized.

205
00:11:52,546 --> 00:11:55,482
>> Someone stop it! (Tominaga) I'm stopping it.

206
00:11:55,549 --> 00:11:57,984
However, I don't listen to anything other than what the director says.

207
00:11:58,051 --> 00:11:59,986
In that case, the second director should tell the director.

208
00:12:00,053 --> 00:12:01,988
Please stop calling me that! (Tsukimura) We too →

209
00:12:02,055 --> 00:12:03,924
Are you going to cooperate?

210
00:12:03,990 --> 00:12:06,426
(Sumimoto) It's full of normal work.

211
00:12:06,493 --> 00:12:07,928
(buzz)

212
00:12:07,994 --> 00:12:09,930
(Himejima) Well, don't say that.

213
00:12:09,996 --> 00:12:11,932
Let's cooperate.

214
00:12:11,998 --> 00:12:14,935
Now that we've accepted a pregnant woman, we should give her a thorough checkup.

215
00:12:15,001 --> 00:12:16,937
As a doctor.

216
00:12:17,003 --> 00:12:19,439
That's a horrifying and unbelievable statement.

217
00:12:19,506 --> 00:12:21,441
(Narumiya) Regarding celebrity customers →

218
00:12:21,508 --> 00:12:24,444
We have been approached privately to request cooperation.

219
00:12:24,511 --> 00:12:26,947
Because I would be in trouble if Mr. Mitsui refused →

220
00:12:27,013 --> 00:12:30,951
I think this is a hasty and pompous statement.

221
00:12:31,017 --> 00:12:33,954
(Himejima) This is a case of architect Ayumi Yada, 44 years old.

222
00:12:34,020 --> 00:12:36,456
(Todo) No, no, there is no objection. (Himejima) As for your husband→

223
00:12:36,523 --> 00:12:40,460
He is the second-generation president of the long-established toy manufacturer Juyado.

224
00:12:40,527 --> 00:12:43,964
I have been undergoing infertility treatment for 6 years, but with no success.

225
00:12:44,030 --> 00:12:45,966
Are you considering egg donation?

226
00:12:46,032 --> 00:12:47,968
(Nagasaka) But it's difficult in Japan.

227
00:12:48,034 --> 00:12:50,470
>> This is a plan to receive egg donation overseas.

228
00:12:50,537 --> 00:12:52,472
If all goes well, give birth →

229
00:12:52,539 --> 00:12:54,474
I'm asking if you can do it for me.

230
00:12:54,541 --> 00:12:56,476
This will be a very high risk birth.

231
00:12:56,543 --> 00:13:00,981
That's why we need Mr. Mitsui's skills.

232
00:13:01,047 --> 00:13:03,416
That smug face makes me angry.

233
00:13:03,483 --> 00:13:07,420
(Mitsui) Are you annoyed? My smug face.

234
00:13:07,487 --> 00:13:09,923
(Himejima) Anyway, to Mr. Yata's interview →

235
00:13:09,990 --> 00:13:12,425
Everyone from each department is welcome to attend.

236
00:13:12,492 --> 00:13:14,427
(Kurata) Eh, why?

237
00:13:14,494 --> 00:13:17,430
I think it's a matter of self-preservation that you don't want to carry alone.

238
00:13:17,497 --> 00:13:19,432
Everyone, please.

239
00:13:19,499 --> 00:13:22,502
(Mitsui) So please do this as well.

240
00:13:27,507 --> 00:13:33,446
(Yada) I heard that my parents got pregnant through egg donation.

241
00:13:33,513 --> 00:13:35,448
Why not give it a try?

242
00:13:35,515 --> 00:13:38,952
Did you know that there are considerable risks?

243
00:13:39,019 --> 00:13:41,955
There are also many gray areas.

244
00:13:42,022 --> 00:13:43,456
(Mitsui) About that →

245
00:13:43,523 --> 00:13:46,459
Detailed information is available in ``Doctor Justice: Infertility Treatment Edition.''

246
00:13:46,526 --> 00:13:48,962
(Ayumi) “Doctor Justice”?

247
00:13:49,029 --> 00:13:51,965
This is a manga that exposes medical history.

248
00:13:52,032 --> 00:13:54,467
what are you talking about? (Todo) Oh no.

249
00:13:54,534 --> 00:13:57,470
Well, I would like to recommend it too.

250
00:13:57,537 --> 00:13:59,973
You can quickly learn about the dark side of infertility treatment.

251
00:14:00,040 --> 00:14:02,475
I'll read it.

252
00:14:02,542 --> 00:14:05,912
Please talk to me from a professional standpoint.

253
00:14:05,979 --> 00:14:08,415
Ah, then.

254
00:14:08,481 --> 00:14:13,920
In addition to age, there are also immune problems, making bleeding during childbirth more likely.

255
00:14:13,987 --> 00:14:16,423
Centralized management is often required.

256
00:14:16,489 --> 00:14:19,926
(Mitsui) In the worst case scenario, the uterus may have to be removed.

257
00:14:19,993 --> 00:14:22,429
>> There is no right to know the origin of children.

258
00:14:22,495 --> 00:14:25,932
(Mitsui) The rest is from Mr. Nagasaka.

259
00:14:25,999 --> 00:14:27,434
(Nagasaka) Yes?

260
00:14:27,500 --> 00:14:30,437
(Mitsui) Is there anything you would like to ask?

261
00:14:30,503 --> 00:14:32,439
(Nagasaka) Ah, um...｡

262
00:14:32,505 --> 00:14:34,941
Ah, please tell me how the two of you met.

263
00:14:35,008 --> 00:14:36,943
>> Encounter? (Nagasaka) Yes.

264
00:14:37,010 --> 00:14:39,012
>>What I want to ask is that?

265
00:14:41,014 --> 00:14:43,450
Both of us have a hobby of touring on motorcycles.

266
00:14:43,516 --> 00:14:45,452
That's how we met.

267
00:14:45,518 --> 00:14:47,954
(Nagasaka) My hobby is mountain climbing. (Todo) Hey.

268
00:14:48,021 --> 00:14:50,457
What is this chat time? (Mitsui) Continue.

269
00:14:50,523 --> 00:14:54,961
(Nagasaka) Well, as far as the progress of the infertility treatment for both of you is concerned, →

270
00:14:55,028 --> 00:14:57,964
I have been going through a lot of trouble these past six years.

271
00:14:58,031 --> 00:15:00,467
Naturally, Ayumi's work must have been affected as well.

272
00:15:00,533 --> 00:15:03,403
However, I will continue the treatment.

273
00:15:03,470 --> 00:15:06,907
After receiving egg donation →

274
00:15:06,973 --> 00:15:09,976
That means you have very strong feelings.

275
00:15:12,979 --> 00:15:15,415
(Nagasaka) Huh? (Mitsui) Not "Huh?"

276
00:15:15,482 --> 00:15:19,419
Yes, that's important.

277
00:15:19,486 --> 00:15:23,423
I want to have a baby no matter what, even if it's a risk.

278
00:15:23,490 --> 00:15:25,425
If you say so→

279
00:15:25,492 --> 00:15:28,995
We will cooperate as much as possible.

280
00:15:33,500 --> 00:15:37,437
(Kurata) Mei-san and Ayumi-san are both at a critical moment.

281
00:15:37,504 --> 00:15:40,940
(Mitsui) Yeah, it's time for us to do our best too.

282
00:15:41,007 --> 00:15:44,945
After all your hard work, it's time for the second mountain drinking party!

283
00:15:45,011 --> 00:15:49,449
(2 people) Yay! (applause)

284
00:15:49,516 --> 00:15:51,451
(Nagasaka) No.

285
00:15:51,518 --> 00:15:54,454
Digging deeper into each pregnant woman and patient →

286
00:15:54,521 --> 00:15:58,024
Honestly, the more I think about it, the more I feel sick.

287
00:16:00,527 --> 00:16:04,397
(Mitsui) It's late, but why did you choose this path?

288
00:16:04,464 --> 00:16:06,399
(Nagasaka) That's why I wanted to take over my parents' hospital...

289
00:16:06,466 --> 00:16:09,903
(Mitsui) It's not like that, it's more like this.

290
00:16:09,969 --> 00:16:11,404
(Nagasaka) Yes?

291
00:16:11,471 --> 00:16:13,406
>> Fundamental in the heart →

292
00:16:13,473 --> 00:16:17,410
It probably means your feelings towards obstetricians and gynecologists.

293
00:16:17,477 --> 00:16:21,481
What, that silence?

294
00:16:22,982 --> 00:16:24,918
(Narumiya) It doesn't really seem like it. (Kurata) Eh.

295
00:16:24,984 --> 00:16:26,920
(Nagasaka) Huh...｡

296
00:16:26,986 --> 00:16:29,422
Is it okay to become a doctor unless you have a special desire?

297
00:16:29,489 --> 00:16:33,426
(Mitsui) No, I don't think it's necessary.→

298
00:16:33,493 --> 00:16:37,931
But if you keep working, it will take up a large part of your life.

299
00:16:37,998 --> 00:16:39,933
Well, there's nothing better than that.

300
00:16:39,999 --> 00:16:41,935
(Nagasaka) Then, what about Mr. Mitsui?

301
00:16:42,001 --> 00:16:44,437
(Mitsui) Hearing the birth cry.

302
00:16:44,504 --> 00:16:48,008
That's what's most important to me.

303
00:16:52,512 --> 00:16:55,949
(Higashida) Continued trial operation of the project at his own discretion.

304
00:16:56,015 --> 00:16:58,952
It is inevitable that a request for dismissal will be filed.

305
00:16:59,018 --> 00:17:01,955
(Kamiya) I recently bought my own ball.

306
00:17:02,022 --> 00:17:03,456
>>Yes?

307
00:17:08,461 --> 00:17:11,398
(Isozaki) Apparently they are having trouble with the project.

308
00:17:11,464 --> 00:17:13,400
(Kamiya) It has already been resolved.

309
00:17:13,466 --> 00:17:14,901
>> Eh.

310
00:17:14,968 --> 00:17:18,972
(Kamiya) There was someone who was buying votes for the board of directors.

311
00:17:20,974 --> 00:17:24,978
The evidence is ready.

312
00:17:29,482 --> 00:17:34,421
(Kamiya) Mr. Higashida will be notified of his transfer tomorrow.

313
00:17:34,487 --> 00:17:37,424
Hokkaido's hockey is the best.

314
00:17:37,490 --> 00:17:40,427
>> Wait, Director, I just want to protect the hospital...

315
00:17:40,493 --> 00:17:44,431
(Shuichi) Looks like you picked a fight with the wrong person.

316
00:17:44,497 --> 00:17:46,433
Please pick it up.

317
00:17:46,499 --> 00:17:48,501
(Shuichi) Please pick it up.

318
00:17:56,509 --> 00:17:57,944
(Isozaki) Shuichi.

319
00:17:58,011 --> 00:18:02,515
Please leave your seat for a while.

320
00:18:05,452 --> 00:18:06,953
yes.

321
00:18:08,955 --> 00:18:11,891
(Isozaki) If I win→

322
00:18:11,958 --> 00:18:14,394
Can I ask you one favor?

323
00:18:14,461 --> 00:18:16,396
(Kamiya) What?

324
00:18:16,463 --> 00:18:19,899
>> Your entry into politics.

325
00:18:19,966 --> 00:18:21,901
I'm not surprised.

326
00:18:21,968 --> 00:18:25,405
(Kamiya) No, I have something to do on site...

327
00:18:25,472 --> 00:18:27,907
(Isozaki) How should we guide obstetric medical care?

328
00:18:27,974 --> 00:18:30,410
Someone who doesn't know the situation takes the reins.

329
00:18:30,477 --> 00:18:32,479
That's why I get lost.

330
00:18:34,481 --> 00:18:37,917
I want you to get out of my basement.

331
00:18:37,984 --> 00:18:41,421
You seem a little surprised.

332
00:18:41,488 --> 00:18:43,923
(Kamiya) Isn't your son going to inherit the foundation?

333
00:18:43,990 --> 00:18:47,427
>> Now, let's resume the match.

334
00:18:47,494 --> 00:18:49,996
It's a battle we can't lose.

335
00:19:02,509 --> 00:19:05,945
Please do this as well. (Female) Thank you.

336
00:19:08,448 --> 00:19:10,950
(May) Mr. Nagasaka?

337
00:19:14,454 --> 00:19:16,389
(Nagasaka) Here are the documents required for hospitalization.

338
00:19:16,456 --> 00:19:18,892
(May) Thank you.

339
00:19:18,958 --> 00:19:22,395
Until I gave birth to a baby thanks to Nao →

340
00:19:22,462 --> 00:19:25,899
I will be able to take time off from work.

341
00:19:25,965 --> 00:19:27,901
(Nagasaka) I will also be in charge of Mei-san.

342
00:19:27,967 --> 00:19:30,904
Nao...

343
00:19:30,970 --> 00:19:33,973
Please talk to Mr. Ayukawa about this.

344
00:19:35,475 --> 00:19:37,977
>> Why don't you say it yourself?

345
00:19:39,479 --> 00:19:41,915
I'm tired of being indecisive.

346
00:19:41,981 --> 00:19:47,921
No courage, no guts, no courage.

347
00:19:47,987 --> 00:19:53,927
That's what Nao said about Nagasaka-sensei.

348
00:19:53,993 --> 00:19:58,932
Just at home and at school→

349
00:19:58,998 --> 00:20:04,504
Because you were kind to me when I didn't have a place to belong.

350
00:20:11,010 --> 00:20:13,012
(Nagasaka) [What are you reading? ]

351
00:20:16,015 --> 00:20:18,952
>> [Why aren't you talking to me? ]

352
00:20:19,018 --> 00:20:21,955
[Do you feel sorry for being alone? Can't you leave me alone? ]

353
00:20:22,021 --> 00:20:25,458
[That kind of makes me angry]

354
00:20:25,525 --> 00:20:28,461
[Sorry] (Nagasaka) [Sorry]

355
00:20:28,528 --> 00:20:30,463
[Eh]

356
00:20:30,530 --> 00:20:34,968
>> [That's why people hate me.]

357
00:20:35,034 --> 00:20:37,971
(Nagasaka) [I don't hate you at all]

358
00:20:38,037 --> 00:20:41,040
[I just wanted to talk]

359
00:20:42,542 --> 00:20:44,477
>> [Are you saying that with a straight face? ]

360
00:20:44,544 --> 00:20:47,046
(Nagasaka) [What, you had a straight face? ] (Nao) [Yeah]

361
00:20:50,049 --> 00:20:51,985
(May's voice) The person I loved.

362
00:20:52,051 --> 00:20:55,488
But he was someone I hated.

363
00:20:55,555 --> 00:20:58,992
He was extremely kind.

364
00:20:59,058 --> 00:21:03,429
But it was extremely cold.

365
00:21:03,496 --> 00:21:07,934
Nao: I'm surprised you say the opposite.

366
00:21:08,001 --> 00:21:10,436
I don't really understand.

367
00:21:10,503 --> 00:21:15,441
Which one is the real teacher?

368
00:21:15,508 --> 00:21:42,035
♪～

369
00:21:45,538 --> 00:21:47,974
It's kind of embarrassing.

370
00:21:48,041 --> 00:21:51,978
Even though I'm a good year old, I was seen crying.

371
00:21:52,045 --> 00:21:56,983
(Mitsui) I think there are days when I want to cry because it's a good year.

372
00:21:57,050 --> 00:22:00,486
>>I came here for treatment.

373
00:22:00,553 --> 00:22:03,923
but….

374
00:22:03,990 --> 00:22:07,427
Remember what Nagasaka-sensei told me.

375
00:22:07,493 --> 00:22:08,928
(Nagasaka) Huh?

376
00:22:08,995 --> 00:22:11,431
[Continue treatment anyway]

377
00:22:11,497 --> 00:22:13,933
[It means that you have very strong feelings.]

378
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:17,937
>> What a strong feeling...

379
00:22:18,004 --> 00:22:21,441
The next day I thought I'd do my best →

380
00:22:21,507 --> 00:22:25,445
I felt depressed just seeing a mother with her baby.

381
00:22:25,511 --> 00:22:30,450
This time, this time →

382
00:22:30,516 --> 00:22:34,954
I wonder when it will end.

383
00:22:35,021 --> 00:22:37,957
(Mitsui) It's painful to have no end, isn't it?

384
00:22:38,024 --> 00:22:40,960
Still, I will continue without giving up.

385
00:22:41,027 --> 00:22:45,965
Or let the two of you separate.

386
00:22:46,032 --> 00:22:51,471
It's difficult to choose something.

387
00:22:51,537 --> 00:22:55,041
But if you don't choose, you can't move forward.

388
00:22:57,543 --> 00:22:59,979
It’s not about someone else’s happiness →

389
00:23:00,046 --> 00:23:04,917
Please think about the happiness of Mr. and Mrs. Yada.

390
00:23:04,984 --> 00:23:07,420
I won't leave you alone.

391
00:23:07,487 --> 00:23:18,431
♪～

392
00:23:18,498 --> 00:23:21,934
(Nagasaka) Mr. Mitsui is very fond of Naniwa-bushi.

393
00:23:22,001 --> 00:23:23,936
(Mitsui) Huh?

394
00:23:24,003 --> 00:23:26,939
(Nagasaka) Words to say to pregnant women and patients →

395
00:23:27,006 --> 00:23:28,941
It's so straight that I'm a little embarrassed →

396
00:23:29,008 --> 00:23:31,944
But there are times when I feel like I'm thinking too much.

397
00:23:32,011 --> 00:23:34,447
(Mitsui) It's a rip-off. (Nagasaka) Rip-off?

398
00:23:34,514 --> 00:23:36,449
(Mitsui) I thought the doctor's words were good.

399
00:23:36,516 --> 00:23:38,451
(Nagasaka) Do you mean someone else's words?

400
00:23:38,518 --> 00:23:42,455
(Mitsui) Every time something happens, I remember something or something that touches my heart.

401
00:23:42,522 --> 00:23:44,457
I tried to make that my true feelings as well.

402
00:23:44,524 --> 00:23:46,459
(Nagasaka) What do you really think?

403
00:23:46,526 --> 00:23:48,528
(Mitsui) That's what you do.

404
00:23:53,533 --> 00:23:54,967
(Keisuke) Teacher.

405
00:23:55,034 --> 00:23:56,969
(Hiroki) What, are you going to give it to the teacher? (Keisuke) Yeah.

406
00:23:57,036 --> 00:23:58,971
(Mother) Your teacher helped you.

407
00:23:59,038 --> 00:24:00,973
(Keisuke) Thank you, teacher!

408
00:24:01,040 --> 00:24:02,975
(Hiroki) Keisuke-kun, you've grown up.

409
00:24:03,042 --> 00:24:05,912
(Hiroki) Yo! what up?

410
00:24:05,978 --> 00:24:08,915
(Nagasaka) I got some time off so I can show you my face.

411
00:24:08,981 --> 00:24:12,418
Why did your father stop delivering babies and switch to specializing in infertility treatment?

412
00:24:12,485 --> 00:24:15,922
I thought it was due to management issues.

413
00:24:15,988 --> 00:24:18,925
>> No, it's hard to say otherwise when you say that.

414
00:24:18,991 --> 00:24:21,928
(Nagasaka) But your father has his own true feelings, right?

415
00:24:21,994 --> 00:24:23,930
>>Ah...｡

416
00:24:23,996 --> 00:24:28,434
I have been involved in childbirth for a long time.

417
00:24:28,501 --> 00:24:32,438
But there are some people who can't give birth even if they want to.

418
00:24:32,505 --> 00:24:38,444
I thought it would be rewarding to be close to those people.

419
00:24:38,511 --> 00:24:41,447
(Nagasaka) Is it worth it?

420
00:24:41,514 --> 00:24:44,450
Dad owns himself.

421
00:24:44,517 --> 00:24:47,453
That's why I still continue this work.

422
00:24:47,520 --> 00:24:52,959
When I was a child, I saw my father being relied on by a pregnant woman →

423
00:24:53,025 --> 00:24:54,961
I thought it was cool.

424
00:24:55,027 --> 00:24:57,029
>> Hahaha…｡

425
00:24:58,531 --> 00:25:01,968
(Nagasaka) That's all I am.

426
00:25:02,034 --> 00:25:04,403
It's surprising how much I don't have myself.

427
00:25:04,470 --> 00:25:06,906
>> Hey, you've said it all.

428
00:25:06,973 --> 00:25:13,412
Well, your strength lies in being able to say that.

429
00:25:13,479 --> 00:25:15,915
Enjoy getting lost.

430
00:25:15,982 --> 00:25:20,419
However, I don't want to say that he won't inherit my house.

431
00:25:20,486 --> 00:25:22,421
(Nagasaka) Hmm, how about that?

432
00:25:22,488 --> 00:25:25,424
>> You hahaha…｡

433
00:25:25,491 --> 00:25:35,935
♪～

434
00:25:36,002 --> 00:25:37,937
(Nagasaka) Yay.

435
00:25:38,004 --> 00:25:47,947
♪～

436
00:25:48,014 --> 00:25:52,952
📱(vibration sound)

437
00:25:53,019 --> 00:25:54,954
(Nagasaka) Yes. 📱(Narumiya) Tomorrow about Mei-san →

438
00:25:55,021 --> 00:25:57,456
Professor Mitsui would like to hold a meeting.

439
00:25:57,523 --> 00:26:01,460
(Nagasaka) Narimiya-san I'm in the mountains now.

440
00:26:01,527 --> 00:26:03,462
I climbed a mountain.

441
00:26:03,529 --> 00:26:05,398
📱 Yes.

442
00:26:05,464 --> 00:26:08,901
(Nagasaka) People don't change even if they climb a mountain.

443
00:26:08,968 --> 00:26:12,905
People don't change even if they climb a mountain.

444
00:26:12,972 --> 00:26:17,977
So I decided to go down the mountain.

445
00:26:23,482 --> 00:26:24,917
(Nagasaka) Ho!

446
00:26:24,984 --> 00:26:29,422
(Kurata) What what what what what? Did anything interesting happen?

447
00:26:29,488 --> 00:26:32,925
Yeah, there's a fine line between being funny and laughing out loud.

448
00:26:32,992 --> 00:26:34,493
Huh!

449
00:26:43,002 --> 00:26:47,440
(Mitsui) May's giant splenic artery aneurysm will be removed through surgery before delivery.

450
00:26:47,506 --> 00:26:49,942
>> Performing such a highly difficult surgery while pregnant.

451
00:26:50,009 --> 00:26:53,946
(Mitsui) Then, we determine the timing of childbirth by looking at the condition of the mother's body.

452
00:26:54,013 --> 00:26:58,451
(Kamiya) If we are to do that, we will need the cooperation of a vascular surgery specialist.

453
00:26:58,517 --> 00:27:00,453
(Nagasaka) Regarding that →

454
00:27:00,519 --> 00:27:02,955
We asked Professor Kagaya of Teito University for his cooperation →

455
00:27:03,022 --> 00:27:04,457
They kindly agreed.

456
00:27:04,523 --> 00:27:06,459
>>Aren't you a leading expert? (Nagasaka) Yes.

457
00:27:06,525 --> 00:27:08,461
Since he is my father's junior, I asked him for help.

458
00:27:08,527 --> 00:27:10,963
(Mayama) A connection with a monk. (Saotome) It's a connection.

459
00:27:11,030 --> 00:27:12,965
(Tsukimura) It's a connection. (Narimiya) Regarding connections →

460
00:27:13,032 --> 00:27:15,468
It seems that some people have negative opinions.

461
00:27:15,534 --> 00:27:19,972
However, connections are something you are born with.

462
00:27:20,039 --> 00:27:21,974
In other words, connections are talent.

463
00:27:22,041 --> 00:27:23,976
(Nagasaka) Yes, connections are talent.

464
00:27:24,043 --> 00:27:26,479
>> Oh, I repeated it confidently.

465
00:27:26,545 --> 00:27:30,483
(Nagasaka) It may be possible to save the lives of both Mei and the baby.

466
00:27:30,549 --> 00:27:31,984
(Todo) Hey.

467
00:27:32,051 --> 00:27:33,986
He suddenly became a hot guy.

468
00:27:34,053 --> 00:27:35,988
Were you influenced by anyone?

469
00:27:36,055 --> 00:27:39,492
(Nagasaka) I have a tendency to get caught up in things.

470
00:27:39,558 --> 00:27:43,929
If so, why not at least try to get involved yourself?

471
00:27:43,996 --> 00:27:46,432
Well, it's a positive inspiration.

472
00:27:46,499 --> 00:27:47,933
>> What? that.

473
00:27:48,000 --> 00:27:50,436
(Nagasaka) Professor Mitsui is not the only person who is inspired.

474
00:27:50,503 --> 00:27:54,440
To all members of the maternal and child emergency department, Director Kamiya and Dr. Tominaga →

475
00:27:54,507 --> 00:27:57,943
Mr. Todo also has solid skills.

476
00:27:58,010 --> 00:27:59,945
>>For some reason, I'm being ignored.

477
00:28:00,012 --> 00:28:02,448
Before I knew it, I was in Nagasaka that I didn't know.

478
00:28:02,515 --> 00:28:04,950
(Kurata) People who are determined are strong.

479
00:28:05,017 --> 00:28:06,952
(Todo) I don't care about newcomers looking for themselves.

480
00:28:07,019 --> 00:28:11,457
Director Kamiya, I would like to say this on this occasion.

481
00:28:11,524 --> 00:28:13,959
Isn't it too beautiful?

482
00:28:14,026 --> 00:28:17,463
Your words and actions are so offensive.

483
00:28:17,530 --> 00:28:19,965
I'm not the only one who thinks so.

484
00:28:20,032 --> 00:28:21,967
yeah?

485
00:28:22,034 --> 00:28:26,472
Celebrities pay a lot of money to secure the best place to give birth.

486
00:28:26,539 --> 00:28:28,474
With the money I got there →

487
00:28:28,541 --> 00:28:30,976
There are pregnant women who receive the best treatment for free.

488
00:28:31,043 --> 00:28:33,479
And they're hiding it from celebrities.

489
00:28:33,546 --> 00:28:35,981
Distribution of wealth is something that the state does.

490
00:28:36,048 --> 00:28:38,484
Who are you?

